<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 9:37PM EDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...Patchy Black Ice and Very Cold Temperatures Tonight...
Snowfall today has resulted in wet roads from snowmelt across the
region. Moisture on untreated roads and surfaces will refreeze
tonight as temperatures drop into the teens and single digits.
Patchy black ice will pose a danger to drivers through Sunday
morning, so use caution, slow down, and allow extra time to reach
your destination.
In addition, very cold air will settle across the area tonight
with temperatures near record low minimums. Please ensure pets and
animals have warm shelter from the cold, protect any sensitive
vegetation, and ensure pipes and crawl spaces are properly
insulated to prevent freezing.</description>
